N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 95.12 - Order of commissioner

State Regulations

If the hearing officer shall find that a respondent has engaged in an unlawful discriminatory practice as defined in section
206-a
of the Public Health Law, the commissioner shall issue and cause to be served on the respondent an order requiring the respondent to cease and desist from the unlawful discriminatory practice. If the hearing officer shall find that a respondent has not engaged in an unlawful discriminatory practice, the commissioner shall issue and cause to be served on the complainant and respondent an order dismissing the complaint as to such respondent.
